From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|palme|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|palma||palm|lang=la}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|päm}}, {{IPA|/pɑːm/}}, {{SAMPA|/pA:m/}}
* {{audio|En-us-palm.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ɑːm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of various [[evergreen]] [[tree]]s from the family ''[[Palmae]]'' or ''[[Arecaceae]]'', which are mainly found in the [[tropics]].
# The inner and somewhat concave part of the human hand that extends from the wrist to the bases of the fingers.
#* '''1990''' October 28, [[w:Paul Simon|Paul Simon]], “Further to Fly”, ''[[w:The Rhythm of the Saints|The Rhythm of the Saints]]'', Warner Bros.
#*: The open '''palm''' of desire wants everything.
# The corresponding part of the forefoot of a lower mammal.
# A handheld computing device used to store personal data such as calendars and phone numbers.

